snippet.title: Need for Machine Learning
snippet.description:
For More Details visit at : http://www.mlminds.com/
ML is needed to mimic humans and automate certain monotonous tasks. Ex. - Recognizing Handwritten characters. ML is needed to discover new knowledge from large databases. ML is needed to develop systems that can automatically adapt and customize themselves to individual users. ML is popular now thanks to availability of large compute power, huge data, new optimized and powerful algorithms and large industry investments.

snippet.title: Is ML too Mathy
snippet.description:
For More Details visit at :http://www.mlminds.com/
Most people think that maths is boring and too difficult. But indeed maths is actually fun and very useful. Although basic usage of ML techniques does not need you to understand any maths behind it, but knowing basic maths will help you  in understanding better. Math skills needed for ML include linear algebra, probability and stats, basic calculus, algorithms, and other related concepts like optimization and information theory.

snippet.title: Data Science Job Roles
snippet.description:
For more Details visit at : http://www.mlminds.com/
Four main types of data science job roles are: (1) Data Analyst/Business Analyst (2) Data engineer/Data Management Professional/Hadoop (3) Data scientist (4) Machine learning engineer. This video describes skills required for these roles.

snippet.title: Planning travel in the age of machine learning
snippet.description:
For More Details : http://www.mlminds.com/
ML has many use cases in the travel industry. It is significantly changing the way people do travel bookings. Based on datasets like airline data, frequent flyer data, social media data and other third party data, ML is powering applications like chatbots, recommender systems, flight price predictions, content curation, sales optimization, dynamic pricing, fraud detection, etc.

snippet.title: The ABC's of Machine Learning
snippet.description:
For More Details : http://www.mlminds.com/
Machine Learning  is a field of study that gives the ability to the computer for self-learn without being explicitly programmed. Popular forms of machine learning include supervised learning, unsupervised learning, semi-supervised learning and reinforcement learning. It manifests itself in various applications like hand-written character recognition, market basket analysis, personalized recommendation systems, predictive modeling, etc. It is popular now because of availability of large amounts of computational power, data and optimized algorithms.
